Definition: [ὑποδέω] from {{g5259}} and {{g1210}}; to bind under one's feet, i.e. put on shoes or sandals
[ὑποδέχομαι] from {{g5259}} and {{g1209}}; to admit under one's roof, i.e. entertain hospitably
[ὑπόδικος] from {{g5259}} and {{g1349}}; under sentence, i.e. (by implication) condemned
[ὑπόδημα] from {{g5265}}; something bound under the feet, i.e. a shoe or sandal
[ὑπογραμμός] from a compound of {{g5259}} and {{g1125}}; an underwriting, i.e. copy for imitation (figuratively)
[ὑποβάλλω] from {{g5259}} and {{g906}}; to throw in stealthily, i.e. introduce by collusion
[ὑποδείκνυμι] from {{g5259}} and {{g1166}}; to exhibit under the eyes, i.e. (figuratively) to exemplify (instruct, admonish)
[ὑπόδειγμα] from {{g5263}}; an exhibit for imitation or warning (figuratively, specimen, adumbration)
[ὑποζώννυμι] from {{g5259}} and {{g2224}}; to gird under, i.e. frap (a vessel with cables across the keel, sides and deck)
[ὑποζύγιον] neuter of a compound of {{g5259}} and {{g2218}}; an animal under the yoke (draught-beast), i.e. (specially), a donkey
[ὑποχωρέω] from {{g5259}} and {{g5562}}; to vacate down, i.e. retire quietly

[ὑπωπιάζω] from a compound of {{g5259}} and a derivative of {{g3700}}; to hit under the eye (buffet or disable an antagonist as a pugilist), i.e. (figuratively) to tease or annoy (into compliance), subdue (one's passions)
[ὑποστρέφω] from {{g5259}} and {{g4762}}; to turn under (behind), i.e. to return (literally or figuratively)
[ὑποστρώννυμι] from {{g5259}} and {{g4766}}; to strew underneath (the feet as a carpet)
[ὑποταγή] from {{g5293}}; subordination
[ὑποτάσσω] from {{g5259}} and {{g5021}}; to subordinate; reflexively, to obey
[ὑποτίθημι] from {{g5259}} and {{g5087}}; to place underneath, i.e. (figuratively) to hazard, (reflexively) to suggest
[ὑποτρέχω] from {{g5259}} and {{g5143}} (including its alternate); to run under, i.e. (specially), to sail past
[ὑποτύπωσις] from a compound of {{g5259}} and a derivative of {{g5179}}; typification under (after), i.e. (concretely) a sketch (figuratively) for imitation
[ὑποφέρω] from {{g5259}} and {{g5342}}; to bear from underneath, i.e. (figuratively) to undergo hardship
[ὑπολήνιον] neuter of a presumed compound of {{g5259}} and {{g3025}}; vessel or receptacle under the press, i.e. lower wine-vat
[ὑπολιμπάνω] a prolonged form for {{g5275}}; to leave behind, i.e. bequeath
[ὑπολαμβάνω] from {{g5259}} and {{g2983}}; to take from below, i.e. carry upward; figuratively, to take up, i.e. continue a discourse or topic; mentally, to assume (presume)
[ὑπολείπω] from {{g5295}} and {{g3007}}; to leave under (behind), i.e. (passively) to remain (survive)
[ὑπόκρισις] from {{g5271}}; acting under a feigned part, i.e. (figuratively) deceit ("hypocrisy")
[ὑποκριτής] from {{g5271}}; an actor under an assumed character (stage-player), i.e. (figuratively) a dissembler ("hypocrite"
[ὑποκάτω] from {{g5259}} and {{g2736}}; down under, i.e. beneath
[ὑποκρίνομαι] middle voice from {{g5259}} and {{g2919}}; to decide (speak or act) under a false part, i.e. (figuratively) dissemble (pretend)
[ὑπομένω] from {{g5259}} and {{g3306}}; to stay under (behind), i.e. remain; figuratively, to undergo, i.e. bear (trials), have fortitude, persevere
[ὑπομιμνήσκω] from {{g5259}} and {{g3403}}; to remind quietly, i.e. suggest to the (middle voice, one's own) memory
[ὑπερηφανία] from {{g5244}}; haughtiness
[ὑπερέχω] from {{g5228}} and {{g2192}}; to hold oneself above, i.e. (figuratively) to excel; participle (as adjective, or neuter as noun) superior, superiority
[ὑπερεντυγχάνω] from {{g5228}} and {{g1793}}; to intercede in behalf of
[ὑπερεκχύνω] from {{g5228}} and the alternate form of {{g1632}}; to pour out over, i.e. (passively) to overflow
[ὑπεροχή] from {{g5242}}; prominence, i.e. (figuratively) superiority (in rank or character)
[ὑπέρογκος] from {{g5228}} and {{g3591}}; bulging over, i.e. (figuratively) insolent
[ὑπερνικάω] from {{g5228}} and {{g3528}}; to vanquish beyond, i.e. gain a decisive victory
[ὑπερήφανος] from {{g5228}} and {{g5316}}; appearing above others (conspicuous), i.e. (figuratively) haughty
[ὑπερπερισσῶς] from {{g5228}} and {{g4057}}; superabundantly, i.e. exceedingly
[ὑπερπερισσεύω] from {{g5228}} and {{g4052}}; to super-abound
[ὕπνος] from an obsolete primary (perhaps akin to {{g5259}} through the idea of subsilience); sleep, i.e. (figuratively) spiritual torpor

[ὑπό] a primary preposition; under, i.e. (with the genitive case) of place (beneath), or with verbs (the agency or means, through); (with the accusative case) of place (whither (underneath) or where (below) or time (when (at)) In the comparative, it retains the same general applications, especially of inferior position or condition, and specially, covertly or moderately.
[ὑπέχω] from {{g5259}} and {{g2192}}; to hold oneself under, i.e. endure with patience
[ὑπήκοος] from {{g5219}}; attentively listening, i.e. (by implication) submissive
[ὑπηρετέω] from {{g5257}}; to be a subordinate, i.e. (by implication) subserve
[ὑπηρέτης] from {{g5259}} and a derivative of ἐρέσσω (to row); an under-oarsman, i.e. (generally) subordinate (assistant, sexton, constable)
[ὑπερπλεονάζω] from {{g5228}} and {{g4121}}; to superabound
[ὑπερυψόω] from {{g5228}} and {{g5312}}; to elevate above others, i.e. raise to the highest position
[ὑπερφρονέω] from {{g5228}} and {{g5426}}; to esteem oneself overmuch, i.e. be vain or arrogant
[ὑπερῷον] neuter of a derivative of {{g5228}}; a higher part of the house, i.e. apartment in the third story
[ὗς] apparently a primary word; a hog ("swine")
[ὑπεραίρομαι] middle voice from {{g5228}} and {{g142}}; to raise oneself over, i.e. (figuratively) to become haughty

[ὑπέρ] a primary preposition; "over", i.e. (with the genitive case) of place, above, beyond, across, or causal, for the sake of, instead, regarding; with the accusative case superior to, more than In the comparative, it retains many of the above applications.
[ὑπαντάω] from {{g5259}} and a derivative of {{g473}}; to go opposite (meet) under (quietly), i.e. to encounter, fall in with
[ὕπανδρος] from {{g5259}} and {{g435}}; in subjection under a man, i.e. a married woman
[ὕπαρξις] from {{g5225}}; existency or proprietorship, i.e. (concretely) property, wealth
[ὑπάντησις] from {{g5221}}; an encounter or concurrence (with {{g1519}} for infinitive, in order to fall in with)

[ὑπάρχω] from {{g5259}} and {{g756}}; to begin under (quietly), i.e. come into existence (be present or at hand); expletively, to exist (as copula or subordinate to an adjective, participle, adverb or preposition, or as an auxiliary to a principal (verb)
[ὑπάρχοντα] neuter plural of present participle active of {{g5225}} as noun; things extant or in hand, i.e. property or possessions
[ὑπεναντίος] from {{g5259}} and {{g1727}}; under (covertly) contrary to, i.e. opposed or (as noun) an opponent
[ὑπείκω] from {{g5259}} and εἴκω (to yield, be "weak"); to surrender
[ὑπερέκεινα] from {{g5228}} and the neuter plural of {{g1565}}; above those parts, i.e. still farther
[ὑπερεκτείνω] from {{g5228}} and {{g1614}}; to extend inordinately
[ὑπεραυξάνω] from {{g5228}} and {{g837}}; to increase above ordinary degree
[ὑπερβαίνω] from {{g5228}} and the base of {{g939}}; to transcend, i.e. (figuratively) to overreach
[ὑπέρακμος] from {{g5228}} and the base of {{g188}}; beyond the "acme", i.e. figuratively (of a daughter) past the bloom (prime) of youth
[ὑπεράνω] from {{g5228}} and {{g507}}; above upward, i.e. greatly higher (in place or rank)
[ὑπερβολή] from {{g5235}}; a throwing beyond others, i.e. (figuratively) supereminence; adverbially (with {{g1519}} or {{g2596}}) pre- eminently
[ὑπερείδω] from {{g5228}} and {{g1492}}; to overlook, i.e. not punish
[ὑπερβαλλόντως] adverb from present participle active of {{g5235}}; excessively
[ὑπερβάλλω] from {{g5228}} and {{g906}}; to throw beyod the usual mark, i.e. (figuratively) to surpass (only active participle supereminent)
[υἱός] apparently a primary word; a "son" (sometimes of animals), used very widely of immediate, remote or figuratively, kinship
[υἱοθεσία] from a presumed compound of {{g5207}} and a derivative of {{g5087}}; the placing as a son, i.e. adoption (figuratively, Christian sonship in respect to God)
[ὑετός] from a primary ὕω (to rain); rain, especially a shower
[ὕδωρ] ,   and genitive case,      ὕδατος, etc. from the base of {{g5205}}; water (as if rainy) literally or figuratively
[ὑδρωπικός] from a compound of {{g5204}} and a derivative of {{g3700}} (as if looking watery); to be "dropsical"
[ὑδροποτέω] from a compound of {{g5204}} and a derivative of {{g4095}}; to be a water-drinker, i.e. to abstain from vinous beverages
[ὑδρία] from {{g5204}}; a water-jar, i.e. receptacle for family supply
[ὑμᾶς] accusative case of {{g5210}}; you (as the objective of a verb or preposition)
[ὕλη] perhaps akin to {{g3586}}; a forest, i.e. (by implication) fuel
[ὑμεῖς] irregular plural of {{g4771}}; you (as subjective of verb)
[Ὑμεναῖος] from Ὑμήν (the god of weddings); "hymenæal"; Hymenæus, an opponent of Christianity
[ὑμέτερος] from {{g5210}}; yours, i.e. pertaining to you
[ὑμῖν] irregular dative case of {{g5210}}; to (with or by) you
[ὑμνέω] from {{g5215}}; to hymn, i.e. sing a religious ode; by implication, to celebrate (God) in song
[ὕμνος] apparently from a simpler (obsolete) form of ὑδέω (to celebrate; probably akin to {{g103}}; compare {{h5667}}); a "hymn" or religious ode (one of the Psalms)
[ὑμῶν] genitive case of {{g5210}}; of (from or concerning) you
[ὑπάγω] from {{g5259}} and {{g71}}; to lead (oneself) under, i.e. withdraw or retire (as if sinking out of sight), literally or figuratively
[ὑπακοή] from {{g5219}}; attentive hearkening, i.e. (by implication) compliance or submission
[ὑπακούω] from {{g5259}} and {{g191}}; to hear under (as a subordinate), i.e. to listen attentively; by implication, to heed or conform to a command or authority
[ὑποστολή] from {{g5288}}; shrinkage (timidity), i.e. (by implication) apostasy
[ὑποστέλλω] from {{g5259}} and {{g4724}}; to withhold under (out of sight), i.e. (reflexively) to cower or shrink, (figuratively) to conceal (reserve)
[ὑπόστασις] from a compound of {{g5259}} and {{g2476}}; a setting under (support), i.e. (figuratively) concretely, essence, or abstractly, assurance (objectively or subjectively)
[ὑποπόδιον] neuter of a compound of {{g5259}} and {{g4228}}; something under the feet, i.e. a foot-rest (figuratively)
[ὑποπνέω] from {{g5259}} and {{g4154}}; to breathe gently, i.e. breeze
[ὑποπλέω] from {{g5259}} and {{g4126}}; to sail under the lee of
[ὑπόνοια] from {{g5282}}; suspicion
[ὑπονοέω] from {{g5259}} and {{g3539}}; to think under (privately), i.e. to surmise or conjecture
[ὑπομονή] from {{g5278}}; cheerful (or hopeful) endurance, constancy
[ὑπόμνησις] from {{g5279}}; a reminding or (reflexively) recollection
